modules.description: Implements the UCB1 algorithm for multi-armed bandit problems, providing functions to select actions, assign rewards, and track performance. Operates on an array of arms, each represented by a custom type, and maintains internal state to balance exploration and exploitation. Useful for scenarios like online advertising or clinical trials where optimal choices must be learned through sequential decision-making.
